name: Justin Trudeau on board! Can Force 1 CC-144 [144615] Taxi and Takeoff from Edmonton Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
Back in May, Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau was in Edmonton for a conference, and I just so happened to be there the weekend he was. Here's his Challenger 604 departing Edmonton international Airport for Ottawa afterwards, as "Can Force 1", the callsign for any Royal Canadian Air Force aircraft with the PM on board (basically our equivalent of "Air Force One"). ATC is included, enjoy!

Thanks for watching!

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

FLIGHT INFO
Operator: Royal Canadian Air Force (RCAF)
Aircraft: Bombardier Challenger 604 (CL60)
Aircraft Name: None
Livery: White
Engines: 2x GE CF34
Registration: 144615
Route: Edmonton (YEG) - Ottawa (YOW)
Callsign: Canforce 01
Runway used: 02
Date filmed: May 20, 2017
Local time: 1400
